This paper proposes a model for protein-protein interaction extraction from scientific literature using knowledge selection. The model uses Transformers to encode context sequences and mutual attention to capture important context features. The paper also mentions the use of entity and relation embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of knowledge bases, which suggests the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of embeddings, which suggests the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
